txt2img tab.label: Sampling method
txt2img tab.hint: Which algorithm to use to produce the image

txt2img tab.label: Sampling steps
txt2img tab.hint: How many times to improve the generated image iteratively; higher values take longer; very low values can produce bad results

txt2img tab.label: Tiling
txt2img tab.hint: Produce an image that can be tiled

txt2img tab.label: full quality
txt2img tab.hint: Use full quality VAE to decode latent samples

txt2img tab.label: face restore
txt2img tab.hint: Run processed image through additional face restoration model

txt2img tab.label: Enable second pass
txt2img tab.hint: Use a similar process as image to image to upscale and/or add detail to the final image. Optionally uses refiner model to enhance image details.

txt2img tab.label: Denoising strength
txt2img tab.hint: Determines how little respect the algorithm should have for image's content. At 0, nothing will change, and at 1 you'll get an unrelated image. With values below 1.0, processing will take less steps than the Sampling Steps slider specifies

txt2img tab.label: Denoise start
txt2img tab.hint: Override denoise strength by stating how early base model should finish and when refiner should start. Only applicable to refiner usage. If set to 0 or 1, denoising strength will be used

txt2img tab.label: Hires steps
txt2img tab.hint: Number of sampling steps for upscaled picture. If 0, uses same as for original

txt2img tab.label: Upscaler
txt2img tab.hint: Which pre-trained model to use for the upscaling process.

txt2img tab.label: Upscale by
txt2img tab.hint: Adjusts the size of the image by multiplying the original width and height by the selected value. Ignored if either Resize width to or Resize height to are non-zero

txt2img tab.label: Force Hires
txt2img tab.hint: Hires runs automatically when Latent upscale is selected, but its skipped when using non-latent upscalers. Enable force hires to run hires with non-latent upscalers

txt2img tab.label: Resize width to
txt2img tab.hint: Resizes image to this width. If 0, width is inferred from either of two nearby sliders

txt2img tab.label: Resize height to
txt2img tab.hint: Resizes image to this height. If 0, height is inferred from either of two nearby sliders

txt2img tab.label: Secondary sampler
txt2img tab.hint: Use specific sampler as fallback sampler if primary is not supported for specific operation

txt2img tab.label: Refiner start
txt2img tab.hint: Refiner pass will start when base model is this much complete (set to 0 or 1 to run after full base model run)

txt2img tab.label: Refiner steps
txt2img tab.hint: Number of steps to use for refiner pass

txt2img tab.label: Secondary CFG Scale
txt2img tab.hint: CFG scale used for refiner pass

txt2img tab.label: Guidance rescale
txt2img tab.hint: Rescale CFG generated noise to avoid overexposed images

txt2img tab.label: Secondary Prompt
txt2img tab.hint: Prompt used for both second encoder in base model (if it exists) and for refiner pass (if enabled)

txt2img tab.label: Secondary negative prompt
txt2img tab.hint: Negative prompt used for both second encoder in base model (if it exists) and for refiner pass (if enabled)

txt2img tab.label: Width
txt2img tab.hint: Image width

txt2img tab.label: Height
txt2img tab.hint: Image height

txt2img tab.label: Batch count
txt2img tab.hint: How many batches of images to create (has no impact on generation performance or VRAM usage)

txt2img tab.label: Batch size
txt2img tab.hint: How many image to create in a single batch (increases generation performance at cost of higher VRAM usage)

txt2img tab.label: cfg scale
txt2img tab.hint: Classifier Free Guidance scale: how strongly the image should conform to prompt. Lower values produce more creative results, higher values make it follow the prompt more strictly; recommended values between 5-10

txt2img tab.label: CLIP skip
txt2img tab.hint: Clip skip is a feature that allows users to control the level of specificity of the prompt, the higher the CLIP skip value, the less deep the prompt will be interpreted. CLIP Skip 1 is typical while some anime models produce better results at  CLIP skip 2

txt2img tab.label: Initial seed
txt2img tab.hint: A value that determines the output of random number generator - if you create an image with same parameters and seed as another image, you'll get the same result

txt2img tab.label: Variation
txt2img tab.hint: Second seed to be mixed with primary seed

txt2img tab.label: Variation strength
txt2img tab.hint: How strong of a variation to produce. At 0, there will be no effect. At 1, you will get the complete picture with variation seed (except for ancestral samplers, where you will just get something)

txt2img tab.label: Resize seed from width
txt2img tab.hint: Make an attempt to produce a picture similar to what would have been produced with same seed at specified resolution

txt2img tab.label: Resize seed from height
txt2img tab.hint: Make an attempt to produce a picture similar to what would have been produced with same seed at specified resolution

txt2img tab.label: Override settings
txt2img tab.hint: If you read in generation parameters through 'Process Image tab' and individual generation parameters should deviate from your system settings, this box will be populated with those settings to override your system configuration for this workflow

process tab.hint: Process all images in a folder

process tab.hint: Use this tab to resize the source image(s) to a chosen target size

process tab.hint: Folder where the images are that you want to process

process tab.label: Show result images
process tab.hint: Enable to show the processed images in the image pane

process tab.label: Resize

process tab.hint: If the dimensions of your source image (e.g. 512x510) deviate from your target dimensions (e.g. 1024x768) this function will fit your upscaled image into your target size image. Excess will be cropped

process tab.label: Secondary Upscaler

img2img tab.label: Fixed
img2img tab.hint: Resize image to target resolution. Unless height and width match, you will get incorrect aspect ratio

img2img tab.label: Crop
img2img tab.hint: Resize the image so that entirety of target resolution is filled with the image. Crop parts that stick out

img2img tab.label: Fill
img2img tab.hint: Resize the image so that entirety of image is inside target resolution. Fill empty space with image's colors

img2img tab.label: Mask blur
img2img tab.hint: How much to blur the mask before processing, in pixels

img2img tab.label: latent noise
img2img tab.hint: fill it with latent space noise

img2img tab.label: latent nothing
img2img tab.hint: fill it with latent space zeroes

models tabs.label: Calculate hash for all models
models tabs.hint: Calculates hash for all available models which may take a very long time

models tabs.label: Weights Clip
models tabs.hint: Forced merged weights to be no heavier than the original model, preventing burn in and overly saturated models

models tabs.label: ReBasin
models tabs.hint: Performs multiple merges with permutations in order to keep more features from both models

models tabs.label: Number of ReBasin Iterations
models tabs.hint: Number of times to merge and permute the model before saving

models tabs.label: cpu
models tabs.hint: Uses cpu and RAM only: slowest but least likely to OOM

models tabs.label: shuffle
models tabs.hint: Loads full model in RAM and calculates on VRAM: Less speedup, suggested for SDXL merges

models tabs.label: cuda
models tabs.hint: Loads models into VRAM automatically unloading current model: fastest option but unlikely to handle SDXL Models without OOM

models tabs.label: Base
models tabs.hint: Text Encoder and a few unaligned keys (1 value)

models tabs.label: In Blocks
models tabs.hint: Downsampling Blocks of the UNet (12 values for SD1.5, 9 values for SDXL)

models tabs.label: Mid Block
models tabs.hint: Central Block of the UNet (1 value)

models tabs.label: Out Block
models tabs.hint: Upsampling Blocks of the UNet (12 values for SD1.5, 9 values for SDXL)

models tabs.label: Preset Interpolation Ratio
models tabs.hint: If two presets are selected, interpolate between them

train tab.hint: Recommended : leave empty or 0~0.35 incrementing sequence: 0, 0.05, 0.15

train tab.label: Create interim images
train tab.hint: Save an image to log directory every N steps, 0 to disable

train tab.hint: Save a copy of embedding to log directory every N steps, 0 to disable

train tab.label: Use current settings for previews
train tab.hint: Read parameters (prompt, etc...) from txt2img tab when making previews

train tab.label: Shuffle tags

settings.label: base model
settings.hint: Main model used for all operations

settings.label: refiner model
settings.hint: Refiner model used for second-pass operations

settings.label: Cached models
settings.hint: The number of models to store in RAM for quick access

settings.label: Cached VAEs
settings.hint: The number of VAE files to store in RAM for quick access

settings.label: VAE model
settings.hint: VAE helps with fine details in the final image and may also alter colors

settings.label: Load models using stream loading method
settings.hint: When loading models attempt stream loading optimized for slow or network storage

settings.label: xFormers
settings.hint: Memory optimization. Non-Deterministic (different results each time)

settings.label: Scaled-Dot-Product
settings.hint: Memory optimization. Non-Deterministic unless SDP memory attention is disabled.

settings.label: Prompt padding
settings.hint: Increase coherency by padding from the last comma within n tokens when using more than 75 tokens

settings.label: Original
settings.hint: Original LDM backend

settings.label: Diffusers
settings.hint: Diffusers backend

settings.label: Autocast
settings.hint: Automatically determine precision during runtime

settings.label: Full
settings.hint: Always use full precision

settings.label: FP32
settings.hint: Use 32-bit floating point precision for calculations

settings.label: FP16
settings.hint: Use 16-bit floating point precision for calculations

settings.label: BF16
settings.hint: Use modified 16-bit floating point precision for calculations

settings.label: Full precision for model (--no-half)
settings.hint: Uses FP32 for the model. May produce better results while using more VRAM and slower generation

settings.label: Full precision for VAE (--no-half-vae)
settings.hint: Uses FP32 for the VAE. May produce better results while using more VRAM and slower generation

settings.label: Upcast sampling
settings.hint: Usually produces similar results to --no-half with better performance while using less memory

settings.label: Attempt VAE roll back for NaN values
settings.hint: Requires Torch 2.1 and NaN check enabled

settings.label: File format
settings.hint: Select file format for images

settings.label: Include metadata
settings.hint: Save image create parameters as metadata tags inside image file

settings.label: Images filename pattern
settings.hint:
Use following tags to define how filenames for images are chosen:
seq, uuid
date, datetime, job_timestamp
generation_number, batch_number
model, model_shortname
model_hash, model_name
sampler, seed, steps, cfg
clip_skip, denoising
hasprompt, prompt, styles
prompt_hash, prompt_no_styles
prompt_spaces, prompt_words
height, width, image_hash

settings.label: Row count
settings.hint: Use -1 for autodetect and 0 for it to be same as batch size

settings.label: Update JSON log file per image
settings.hint: Save image information to a JSON file

settings.label: Directory name pattern
settings.hint: Use following tags to define how subdirectories for images and grids are chosen: [steps], [cfg],[prompt_hash], [prompt], [prompt_no_styles], [prompt_spaces], [width], [height], [styles], [sampler], [seed], [model_hash], [model_name], [prompt_words], [date], [datetime], [datetime<Format>], [datetime<Format><Time Zone>], [job_timestamp]; leave empty for default

settings.label: Inpainting conditioning mask strength
settings.hint: Determines how strongly to mask off the original image for inpainting and img2img. 1.0 means fully masked (default). 0.0 means a fully unmasked conditioning. Lower values will help preserve the overall composition of the image, but will struggle with large changes

settings.label: Clip skip
settings.hint: Early stopping parameter for CLIP model; 1 is stop at last layer as usual, 2 is stop at penultimate layer, etc

settings.label: Images folder
settings.hint: If empty, defaults to three directories below

settings.label: Grids folder
settings.hint: If empty, defaults to two directories below

settings.label: Quicksettings list
settings.hint: List of setting names, separated by commas, for settings that should go to the quick access bar at the top instead the setting tab

settings.label: Live preview display period
settings.hint: Request preview image every n steps, set to 0 to disable

settings.label: Approximate
settings.hint: Cheap neural network approximation. Very fast compared to VAE, but produces pictures with 4 times smaller horizontal/vertical resolution and lower quality

settings.label: Simple
settings.hint: Very cheap approximation. Very fast compared to VAE, but produces pictures with 8 times smaller horizontal/vertical resolution and extremely low quality

settings.label: Progress update period
settings.hint: Update period for UI progress bar and preview checks, in miliseconds

settings.label: Euler a
settings.hint: Euler Ancestral - very creative, each can get a completely different picture depending on step count, setting steps higher than 30-40 does not help

settings.label: DPM adaptive
settings.hint: Ignores step count - uses a number of steps determined by the CFG and resolution

settings.label: DDIM
settings.hint: Denoising Diffusion Implicit Models - best at inpainting

settings.label: UniPC
settings.hint: Unified Predictor-Corrector Framework for Fast Sampling of Diffusion Models

settings.label: sigma negative guidance minimum
settings.hint: Skip negative prompt for some steps when the image is almost ready, 0=disable

settings.label: Filename word regex
settings.hint: This regular expression will be used extract words from filename, and they will be joined using the option below into label text used for training. Leave empty to keep filename text as it is

settings.label: Filename join string
settings.hint: This string will be used to join split words into a single line if the option above is enabled

settings.label: Tensorboard flush period
settings.hint: How often, in seconds, to flush the pending Tensorboard events and summaries to disk

settings.label: Interrogate: minimum description length
settings.hint: Interrogate: minimum description length (excluding artists, etc..)

settings.label: CLIP: maximum number of lines in text file
settings.hint: CLIP: maximum number of lines in text file (0 = No limit)

settings.label: Escape brackets in deepbooru
settings.hint: Escape (\) brackets in deepbooru so they are used as literal brackets and not for emphasis

settings.label: Filter out tags from deepbooru output
settings.hint: Filter out those tags from deepbooru output (separated by comma)

settings.label: Upscaler tile size
settings.hint: 0 = no tiling

settings.label: Upscaler tile overlap
settings.hint: Low values = visible seam

settings.label: GFPGAN
settings.hint: Restore low quality faces using GFPGAN neural network

settings.label: CodeFormer weight parameter
settings.hint: 0 = maximum effect; 1 = minimum effect

settings.label: Token merging ratio for txt2img
settings.hint: Enable redundant token merging via tomesd for speed and memory improvements, 0=disabled

settings.label: Token merging ratio for img2img
settings.hint: Enable redundant token merging for img2img via tomesd for speed and memory improvements, 0=disabled

settings.label: Token merging ratio for hires
settings.hint: Enable redundant token merging for hires pass via tomesd for speed and memory improvements, 0=disabled

settings.label: Diffusers pipeline
settings.hint: If autodetect does not detect model automatically, select model type before loading a model

settings.label: Sequential CPU offload (--lowvram)
settings.hint: Reduces GPU memory usage by transferring weights to the CPU. Increases inference time approximately 10%

settings.label: Model CPU offload (--medvram)
settings.hint: Transferring of entire models to the CPU, negligible impact on inference time while still providing some memory savings

settings.label: VAE slicing
settings.hint: Decodes batch latents one image at a time with limited VRAM. Small performance boost in VAE decode on multi-image batches

settings.label: VAE tiling
settings.hint: Divide large images into overlapping tiles with limited VRAM. Results in a minor increase in processing time

settings.label: Attention slicing
settings.hint: Performs attention computation in steps instead of all at once. Slower inference times, but greatly reduced memory usage

settings.label: inference-mode
settings.hint: Use torch.inference_mode

settings.label: no-grad
settings.hint: Use torch.no_grad

settings.label: model compile precompile
settings.hint: Run model compile immediately on model load instead of first use

settings.label: force zeros for prompts when empty
settings.hint: Force full zero tensor when prompt is empty to remove any residual noise

settings.label: require aesthetics score
settings.hint: Automatically guide model towards higher-pleasing results, applicable only to refiner model

settings.label: include watermark
settings.hint: Add invisible watermark to image by altering some pixel values

settings.label: watermark string
settings.hint: Watermark string to add to image. Keep very short to avoid image corruption.

settings.label: show log view
settings.hint: Show log view at the bottom of the main window

settings.label: Log view update period
settings.hint: Log view update period, in miliseconds

scripts.label: X values
scripts.hint: Separate values for X axis using commas

scripts.label: Y values
scripts.hint: Separate values for Y axis using commas

scripts.label: Loops
scripts.hint: How many times to process an image. Each output is used as the input of the next loop. If set to 1, behavior will be as if this script were not used

scripts.label: Final denoising strength
scripts.hint: The denoising strength for the final loop of each image in the batch

scripts.label: Denoising strength curve
scripts.hint: The denoising curve controls the rate of denoising strength change each loop. Aggressive: Most of the change will happen towards the start of the loops. Linear: Change will be constant through all loops. Lazy: Most of the change will happen towards the end of the loops

scripts.label: Tile overlap
scripts.hint: For SD upscale, how much overlap in pixels should there be between tiles. Tiles overlap so that when they are merged back into one picture, there is no clearly visible seam
